snippet.textDisplay:
For the pushup portion of the test, you must keep the pushup position at all times. No sticking your butt up or knees down for rest.
For the swim portion breast stroke or side stroke is only allowed and no resting allowed by standing in the pool or holding on the sides of the pool.
The sit-up portion was done correctly. (Super impressed btw)
For the pullups, palms have to be facing away from you. Hands, shoulder-width apart. No swinging or kicking allowed, no taking either hand off the bar for rest and chin above the bar for it to count.
Overall though, you did very well considering you haven't been practicing to pass this test. I would want to see a second attempt after a few months.

snippet.textDisplay: Nice video, good effort! Im a former arctic paratrooper and tried this test a few weeks ago. Honestly without sounding like a douche, it was extremely easy compared to the tests Im used to. Where Im from we did jogging in deep snow 1.8km within 10-12min time, then pushups til failure minimum 70 then without rest pullups til failure minimum 15 then 3min rest jumping squats til failure minimum 30 superset with hanging leg raises minimum 20, finishing with 90sec in ice cold water answering questions and controlling breathing. After that we went in a hot sauna for recovery

snippet.textDisplay:
The documentary Human Harvest was shown at universities and libraries in Virginia Beach, Richmond, Williamsburg, Henrico, and Charlottesville, all in Virginia, on October 17-21, 2019. A Q&A session followed each screening.

Canadian human rights lawyer David Matas and representative of Doctors Against Forced Organ Harvesting (DAFOH) Dr. Jessica D. Russo were present to answer questions from the audience after the screening.

The film covers the independent investigations carried out by David Matas and former Canadian Secretary of State (Asia Pacific) David Kilgour into the organ trade in China, where organs are taken without consent from prisoners of conscience, as well as documents the communist regime's crimes against humanity.
